      "end": 11.48,
      "text": "and for more information or to volunteer, please visit LibraVox.org.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-003",
      "start": 12.86,
      "end": 18.3,
      "text": "This recording is done by Christen Luoma, green-k-r-i.com.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-004",
      "start": 19.94,
      "end": 23.84,
      "text": "ASOP's Fables, the Tortoise and the Eagle.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-005",
      "start": 26.58,
      "end": 31.54,
      "text": "A Tortoise, discontented with his lowly life and envious of the birds he saw",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-006",
      "start": 31.54,
      "end": 35.34,
      "text": "disporting themselves in the air, begged an eagle to teach him to fly.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-007",
      "start": 36.18,
      "end": 40.92,
      "text": "The eagle protested that it was idle for him to try, as nature had not provided him with wings.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-008",
      "start": 42.0,
      "end": 45.44,
      "text": "But the tortoise pressed him within treaties and promises of treasure,",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-009",
      "start": 46.14,
      "end": 49.46,
      "text": "insisting that it could only be a question of learning the craft of the air.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-010",
      "start": 50.38,
      "end": 53.84,
      "text": "So at length the eagle consented to do the best he could for him,",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-011",
      "start": 54.34,
      "end": 56.02,
      "text": "and picked him up in his talons.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-012",
      "start": 56.9,
      "end": 60.96,
      "text": "Soring with him to a great height in the sky, he then let him go,",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-013",
      "start": 61.86,
      "end": 66.44,
      "text": "and the wretched tortoise fell, headlong, and was dashed to pieces on a rock.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-014",
      "start": 69.2,
      "end": 72.54,
      "text": "End of the Tortoise and the Eagle of ASOP's Fables.",
      "note": ""
    }
  ],
